These are planning numbers, not results. The lever arm is short (a factor of two in N) and the extrapolation to N=600 is a factor of ten beyond it. A power law fits a few small-N points perfectly well even when the true scaling is exponential -- in which case every cost above is an underestimate, and not by a little.

